Here is a simple CSS code to style a button with a bright green background and white text:
```
.button {
  background-color: #34C759; /* bright green */
  color: #FFFFFF; /* white */
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.button:hover {
  background-color: #2ECC40; /* darker green on hover */
}
```
You can apply this CSS code to a button element in your HTML file by adding the class `button` to the button element, like this:
```
<button class="button">Click me!</button>
```
This will give your button a bright green background and white text. The `:hover` pseudo-class is used to change the background color to a darker green when the button is hovered over.

You can adjust the values of the properties to change the appearance of the button. For example, you can change the `background-color` value to a different shade of green, or adjust the `padding` and `border-radius` values to change the size and shape of the button.

